{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"e312c636-e89a-46be-a59b-2b041c42540b","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/findings-parse-soundness/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/findings-parse-soundness/design.md","title":"D4 residual risk: manifest-shaped JSON array still misclassified as directory","rationale":"A file whose first JSON element has both `name: string` and `type: string` fields (e.g. a manifest with `[{ type: \"file\", name: \"...\" }]` entries) will still trigger `isGitHubDirectoryListing` and be misclassified. The design acknowledges this and calls out the `sha` field as a future mitigation. Acceptable for this bug-fix scope given the dramatically reduced false-positive surface."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/findings-parse-soundness/tasks.md","title":"T-07 wording: testing a private function via direct export is the wrong default","rationale":"`isGitHubDirectoryListing` is declared file-scoped (not exported) in design.md, but T-07 lists testing it directly as the primary option before the end-to-end mock alternative. Implementers should prefer the mock-`verifyFindingRefs` path to avoid leaking a test-only export into production code."}],"observations":[{"severity":"medium","file":"src/core/port/report-result.ts","title":"Bug (a) confirmed: `parseFindings` missing `f[\"line\"] !== null` guard","rationale":"`parseObservations` line 232 already has `o[\"line\"] !== null` in the guard; `parseFindings` line 162 does not. `null` satisfies `!== undefined` and `typeof null !== \"number\"`, so any finding with `line: null` causes the entire array to be rejected. Asymmetry confirmed in source.","line":162},{"severity":"medium","file":"src/adapter/codex/agent-runner.ts","title":"Bug (b) confirmed: `stripNullDeep` in codex path only — runtime split","rationale":"`stripNullDeep(json)` is called before `parseInput` in the codex path, masking the line 162 defect. Local and managed runtimes go directly through `parseFindings` without null stripping. Same agent output passes in codex and fails in local/managed.","line":179},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/parser/review-scores.ts","title":"Bug (c) confirmed: `parseReviewScores` has zero production callers","rationale":"grep across src/ shows `parseReviewScores` is only defined, never called. `ParsedStepResult.scores` in step-types.ts is declared but never set or read. Dead path confirmed; deletion is correct."},{"severity":"medium","file":"src/core/runtime/managed.ts","title":"Bug (d) confirmed: `Array.isArray(parsed)` misclassifies any JSON array file as a directory","rationale":"Any file whose content is a top-level JSON array (test fixtures, lock excerpts, schemas) is classified as a directory and the finding is pushed to `nonExistent`. The shape-based `isGitHubDirectoryListing` fix correctly narrows detection to GitHub directory entry format.","line":351},{"severity":"low","file":"src/adapter/github/github-client.ts","title":"Security: `ref.file` path traversal mitigated by `encodeURIComponent`","rationale":"`filePath.split(\"/\").map(encodeURIComponent).join(\"/\")` encodes each path segment before the GitHub API call. Agent-supplied `file` fields cannot perform path traversal beyond what the GitHub API boundary already enforces.","line":154}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-25T10:56:25.430Z","endedAt":"2026-06-25T10:59:57.725Z"}
